WEBVTT

00:02.069 --> 00:04.870
Richard: My father
wanted a grandson.

00:04.872 --> 00:07.506
And when I say "wanted,"
I mean he all but insisted.

00:07.508 --> 00:08.540
[ Chuckles ]

00:08.542 --> 00:10.709
As you know,
biology doesn't work that way.

00:10.711 --> 00:14.046
So out came Vanessa,
a girl.

00:14.048 --> 00:16.281
And I'll tell you,
Jake old pal,

00:16.283 --> 00:19.385
when I saw
that cute little face of hers,

00:19.387 --> 00:21.553
I didn't give a rat's ass
what my father thought.

00:21.555 --> 00:22.554
[ Laughs ]

00:22.556 --> 00:25.257
[ Chuckles ]
Thank you.

00:29.630 --> 00:33.165
Anyhow, this is
my long-winded way of saying

00:33.167 --> 00:35.467
that you're the son
I never thought I wanted.

00:40.341 --> 00:43.375
To have you here as part
of our family, that just...

00:46.514 --> 00:48.480
...just...

00:48.482 --> 00:50.349
Ohh!

00:50.351 --> 00:52.217
Ohh!

00:52.219 --> 00:54.153
[ Inhales sharply ]
Call 911!

00:55.156 --> 00:57.056
Ohh.

00:57.058 --> 01:00.559
[ Panting ]

01:00.561 --> 01:02.728
What are you waiting for?
I'm sorry, sir.

01:02.730 --> 01:05.230
I'm touched that you think of me
as a son,

01:05.232 --> 01:06.932
but there's another man...

01:06.934 --> 01:09.101
who thinks of me
as his son, too.

01:09.103 --> 01:12.104
And he feels
that Vanessa's inheritance

01:12.106 --> 01:14.573
will open some important doors
for us.

01:15.743 --> 01:17.910
[ Groans ]

01:17.912 --> 01:19.878
[ Body thuds ]

01:19.880 --> 01:21.547
[ Groans ]

01:21.549 --> 01:24.550
♪♪

01:24.552 --> 01:29.121
It's only
a few more seconds.

01:29.123 --> 01:31.190
[ Panting ]

01:32.460 --> 01:34.359
[ Groans ]

01:34.361 --> 01:36.428
Almost there.

01:36.430 --> 01:43.202
♪♪

01:55.783 --> 01:58.083
Operator,
I have an emergency.

01:58.085 --> 01:59.284
Oh, God.

01:59.286 --> 02:01.353
I hope
it's not too late.

02:09.230 --> 02:13.232
[ Door opens ]
[ Laughing ]

02:13.234 --> 02:14.566
Thomas! [ Laughs ]

02:14.568 --> 02:16.935
The<i> Trib</i> is
up its own ass again.

02:16.937 --> 02:19.471
You should see who they think
we're talking to for VP.

02:19.473 --> 02:21.140
Like we'd go with Simmons?

02:21.142 --> 02:23.909
The man
looks like a troll.

02:23.911 --> 02:26.211
What?

02:27.815 --> 02:31.416
Is that...?

02:31.418 --> 02:33.485
Tom: He's renting
an apartment in Virginia.

02:33.487 --> 02:34.920
It's under
his aunt's name.

02:34.922 --> 02:36.955
She signed the lease for him,
did all the paperwork.

02:36.957 --> 02:38.690
Is Ella
going to school?

02:38.692 --> 02:40.125
No, but he's hired
her a tutor -- a couple
of them, actually.

02:40.127 --> 02:41.827
One for
all the academic stuff,

02:41.829 --> 02:43.462
and another one
for art and music.

02:43.464 --> 02:44.830
[ Sighs ]

02:44.832 --> 02:47.199
What do you want to do?

02:47.201 --> 02:50.102
Finish my coffee.

02:50.104 --> 02:53.272
And then pick a VP.

02:53.274 --> 02:54.506
[<i> Camera shutter clicking</i> ]

02:54.508 --> 02:56.041
All this week,
the "Liberty Report"

02:56.043 --> 02:58.677
will be coming to you live
from the Republican convention

02:58.679 --> 03:00.279
here in Baltimore.

03:00.281 --> 03:03.615
Behind me,
the splendid Grant Arena.

03:03.617 --> 03:05.050
Named for the famous general,

03:05.052 --> 03:07.352
not the man-child
that's been soiling his pants

03:07.354 --> 03:10.455
at 1600 Pennsylvania Avenue
for the last eight years.

03:10.457 --> 03:12.858
The question
for both parties this week --

03:12.860 --> 03:16.128
Who will the two candidates,
Frankie Vargas and Mellie Grant,

03:16.130 --> 03:19.464
pick to be their respective
vice presidents?

03:19.466 --> 03:20.966
Cut.

03:20.968 --> 03:22.467
[<i> Camera shutter clicking</i> ]

03:22.469 --> 03:24.169
Let's make this fast.
[ Door closes ]

03:24.171 --> 03:25.571
I know it's hard
for you to believe,

03:25.573 --> 03:27.072
but I have more important
things to do

03:27.074 --> 03:28.707
than expunge
your speeding tickets.

03:28.709 --> 03:31.043
How would you like to be
Frankie Vargas' running mate?

03:32.246 --> 03:33.712
You said make it fast.

03:33.714 --> 03:34.713
Vice President?

03:34.715 --> 03:36.315
Vice president.

03:36.317 --> 03:37.583
Of the
United States of America?

03:37.585 --> 03:39.351
Well, now I'm not so sure.
You seem kind of slow.

03:39.353 --> 03:40.519
Yeah, n--
I'm not slow.

03:40.521 --> 03:44.356
It's just -- Come on.
What's the hitch?

03:44.358 --> 03:46.358
What do you get
out of making me Vice President?

03:46.360 --> 03:49.061
I get David Rosen,
a bright, seasoned, Democrat

03:49.063 --> 03:51.597
who dutifully served
a Republican President.

03:51.599 --> 03:54.900
That's the kind of
honest-across-the-aisle soldier

03:54.902 --> 03:57.903
we need in support
of a charismatic

03:57.905 --> 04:02.407
but admittedly somewhat leftist
leader in Frankie Vargas.

04:02.409 --> 04:04.509
No, I mean, whom do I
have to kill for you...

04:04.511 --> 04:05.777
or imprison for you?

04:05.779 --> 04:08.280
What does the Dark Lord Master
Cyrus Beene want

04:08.282 --> 04:09.514
in return for this?

04:09.516 --> 04:12.517
I did dabble in darkness
for the last decade or so.

04:12.519 --> 04:14.553
I'll admit that.

04:14.555 --> 04:17.189
But then I met Frankie.

04:17.191 --> 04:20.292
Let me tell you,
Rosen.

04:20.294 --> 04:21.727
He's...

04:21.729 --> 04:25.030
once in a lifetime.

04:25.032 --> 04:27.633
He wants to make the world
a better place,

04:27.635 --> 04:31.103
actually make the world
a better place.

04:31.105 --> 04:34.039
You two are cut
from the same cloth.

04:34.041 --> 04:37.476
♪♪

04:37.478 --> 04:39.077
We've narrowed it down
to three VP candidates.

04:39.079 --> 04:40.712
They still need to be vetted,
but each of them

04:40.714 --> 04:42.547
are excellent options,
all possessing the three M's.

04:42.549 --> 04:44.082
The three M's?

04:44.084 --> 04:46.151
Male, married,
and military.

04:46.153 --> 04:49.454
Alden McKay served two terms
as governor of Nevada,

04:49.456 --> 04:50.756
a swing state.

04:50.758 --> 04:52.958
He's pro-life, pro-guns,
pro-all-things-Republican.

04:52.960 --> 04:54.226
I know
what you're getting at.

04:54.228 --> 04:55.994
Besides a speeding ticket
a few years ago,

04:55.996 --> 04:57.262
I'd say
I'm squeaky clean.

04:57.264 --> 04:58.730
He's squeaky clean,
all right.

04:58.732 --> 05:00.432
Before he joined the Marines,
his side gig

05:00.434 --> 05:02.100
was giving late-night
scrub and tugs

05:02.102 --> 05:04.002
to rich foreign dudes
at an after-hours bath house.

05:04.004 --> 05:05.837
"Scrub and tug?"
It's when a man
gets his --

05:05.839 --> 05:07.839
[ Gasps ] Never mind.
I figured it out.

05:07.841 --> 05:09.975
Quinn:
Senator Joe Walton from Texas.

05:09.977 --> 05:12.644
Ex-Navy SEAL, married to
his high-school sweetheart,

05:12.646 --> 05:15.147
loved by his
fellow conservatives because...

05:15.149 --> 05:17.616
I believe taxes
are way too high.

05:17.618 --> 05:19.318
People should keep
their money.

05:19.320 --> 05:21.620
Nobody's better at keeping
his money than the Senator.

05:21.622 --> 05:23.322
When he was 26,
he was a part of a scheme

05:23.324 --> 05:25.090
that involved
selling expired condoms.

05:25.092 --> 05:27.859
He made $475,000.

05:27.861 --> 05:29.294
Never reported it
to the IRS.

05:29.296 --> 05:30.495
How'd you find
that out?

05:30.497 --> 05:32.030
You don't want to know.

05:32.032 --> 05:34.266
Governor Bill Wagner
of Missouri.

05:34.268 --> 05:36.601
Governor Wagner graduated
from Columbia,

05:36.603 --> 05:38.303
served in the Senate for eight
years before becoming governor,

05:38.305 --> 05:40.505
highly respected
by the far right.

05:40.507 --> 05:41.840
I was
a coke dealer.

05:41.842 --> 05:43.008
Excuse me?

05:43.010 --> 05:44.710
Back in college.

05:44.712 --> 05:46.712
I used the money
to pay off my student loans.

05:46.714 --> 05:49.281
Even flew to Bogota
a couple of times.

05:49.283 --> 05:50.782
I didn't do it
for very long,

05:50.784 --> 05:52.651
and only one person in the world
knows about it.

05:52.653 --> 05:54.286
But it happened.

05:54.288 --> 05:57.489
I would love nothing more
than to be your Vice President,

05:57.491 --> 06:00.826
and I would hate to be defined
by the sins of my past.

06:00.828 --> 06:03.128
That said,
I think it's only fair

06:03.130 --> 06:05.397
you know everything about me
before you make your decision --

06:05.399 --> 06:08.200
the good
and the bad.

06:08.202 --> 06:09.201
He's perfect.

06:09.203 --> 06:10.836
We couldn't even
dream him up.

06:10.838 --> 06:12.537
Even Democrats love him.
But cocaine?

06:12.539 --> 06:14.373
Cocaine aside,
he has everything we need --

06:14.375 --> 06:16.475
military experience,
charisma, family man...
Don't forget felon.

06:16.477 --> 06:18.510
He didn't lie about it.
That says something.

06:18.512 --> 06:19.978
Think we can clean him up
in time?

06:19.980 --> 06:20.979
We can try.

06:20.981 --> 06:22.647
Good. Get on it.

06:22.649 --> 06:23.982
[ Door opens ]

06:27.187 --> 06:30.155
Edison,
what are you doing here?

06:30.157 --> 06:32.924
[ Echoing ]
Tell Liv I need her help.

06:32.926 --> 06:34.092
Tell her
I want to escape.

06:34.094 --> 06:35.894
Tell I'm chasing
the sun.

06:35.896 --> 06:38.697
[ Sighs ]
Jake said that?

06:38.699 --> 06:40.932
He's your father's prisoner,
Liv...

06:40.934 --> 06:42.601
his puppet,
just like I was.

06:46.840 --> 06:49.541
Well, I appreciate you
delivering the message, Edison.

06:49.543 --> 06:50.876
It was
very kind of you.

06:50.878 --> 06:52.377
Unfortunately, though,

06:52.379 --> 06:53.945
I do have a convention
to prepare for, so --

06:53.947 --> 06:56.047
That's it? He's asking you
for a life raft, Liv.

06:56.049 --> 06:58.450
I understand that.
I'm not asking you
if you understand.

06:58.452 --> 07:00.018
I'm asking you
what are you gonna do about it?

07:00.020 --> 07:03.188
♪♪

07:03.190 --> 07:04.589
I see.

07:04.591 --> 07:06.792
It's not like that.
Sure it isn't.

07:08.228 --> 07:09.227
[ Sighs ]
[ Door opens ]

07:09.229 --> 07:10.595
Liv.
What?!

07:10.597 --> 07:11.930
[ Door closes ]

07:11.932 --> 07:14.266
You might want
to reconsider.

07:14.268 --> 07:15.767
♪♪

07:15.769 --> 07:17.969
Vanessa's father?

07:17.971 --> 07:20.238
It says he died of a
heart attack, but we
both know that's a lie.

07:20.240 --> 07:22.607
Vanessa just inherited
half a billion dollars.

07:22.609 --> 07:24.409
Your father's building
a war chest.

07:24.411 --> 07:26.645
He's planning something,
and whatever it is,

07:26.647 --> 07:28.613
you know
he's gonna drag Jake into it.

07:28.615 --> 07:29.648
You need
to save him.

07:29.650 --> 07:30.882
I can't.
Liv!

07:30.884 --> 07:32.150
I can't!

07:32.152 --> 07:33.618
My father
will kill him.

07:33.620 --> 07:35.887
If he even thinks that I tried
to help him, he'll kill him.

07:35.889 --> 07:37.088
You know that.

07:37.090 --> 07:40.292
♪♪

07:40.294 --> 07:41.660
[<i> Camera shutter clicking</i> ]

07:41.662 --> 07:43.094
No doubt I can beat
Mellie Grant.

07:43.096 --> 07:45.096
Her weaknesses
are my strengths,

07:45.098 --> 07:47.666
and my campaign manager,
Cyrus Beene, has a tremendous --

07:47.668 --> 07:50.669
Speak of the devil.

07:50.671 --> 07:52.103
Mr. Beene.

07:52.105 --> 07:53.505
Eli Pope.
Pleasure.

07:53.507 --> 07:54.940
Indeed.

07:54.942 --> 07:57.075
Eli was considering
throwing his support behind us.

07:57.077 --> 07:58.577
$30 million worth
of support.

07:58.579 --> 08:00.345
How generous.

08:00.347 --> 08:04.683
That kind of cash
screams super PAC,

08:04.685 --> 08:06.351
and campaign finance laws
forbid the candidate

08:06.353 --> 08:07.953
from having any dealing.

08:07.955 --> 08:10.021
Enough said.

08:10.023 --> 08:14.359
It's nice
to meet you, Eli.

08:17.097 --> 08:18.196
You're not welcome here.

08:18.198 --> 08:20.098
If I only went
where I was welcome,

08:20.100 --> 08:21.266
I'd never
leave the house.

08:21.268 --> 08:23.702
Go on, get to it.
Make your idle threat.

08:23.704 --> 08:26.972
How would Frankie feel knowing
that he was a paper champion,

08:26.974 --> 08:28.840
a puppet?

08:28.842 --> 08:31.009
That the shooting in Harrisburg
was nothing more than theater?

08:31.011 --> 08:32.711
That his campaign manager
engineered murder

08:32.713 --> 08:34.779
to make him a hero?

08:37.518 --> 08:38.717
What do you want?

08:38.719 --> 08:40.352
For your candidate
to win.

08:40.354 --> 08:41.386
Okay.

08:41.388 --> 08:45.123
Put Jake Ballard
on the ticket as VP.

08:49.663 --> 08:50.996
[<i> Camera shutter clicks</i> ]

08:50.998 --> 08:52.230
Doug Morton?
Yeah.

08:52.232 --> 08:54.132
Hi.
That's me.
What can I do you for?

08:54.134 --> 08:56.535
Maybe you want to start
a college fund, secure a loan,

08:56.537 --> 08:58.470
maybe start planning
for retirement?

08:58.472 --> 09:00.472
[<i> Camera shutter clicking</i> ]

09:00.474 --> 09:02.807
I'm sorry.
Who's Anthony Musser?

09:02.809 --> 09:03.975
He's you.
You're him.

09:03.977 --> 09:06.211
No.
See, I-I'm Doug.

09:06.213 --> 09:07.746
Doug Morton.

09:07.748 --> 09:09.080
Anthony Musser
is your new identity.

09:09.082 --> 09:10.315
Passport,
driver's license,

09:10.317 --> 09:13.418
and a deed to a two-bedroom
condo in Albuquerque.

09:13.420 --> 09:14.920
Albuquerque?

09:14.922 --> 09:16.354
You did a bad thing,
Anthony.

09:16.356 --> 09:19.724
Dealing cocaine
with Bill Wagner.

09:19.726 --> 09:21.192
Can't risk that
getting out.

09:21.194 --> 09:22.994
I have no idea
what you're talking about.

09:22.996 --> 09:24.529
[ Quinn chuckles ]

09:24.531 --> 09:26.898
Well, look, that was like
35 years ago, okay?

09:26.900 --> 09:28.867
A-And y-y-you people...

09:28.869 --> 09:30.902
I'm gonna call
the cops.

09:30.904 --> 09:32.938
No, you're not,
Anthony.

09:32.940 --> 09:33.705
No, you're not
calling the cops.

09:33.707 --> 09:35.073
Th-This is insane.

09:35.075 --> 09:36.942
My name is Doug --
Doug Morton.

09:36.944 --> 09:38.710
And I am not
moving to Alb--

09:38.712 --> 09:41.046
You are moving
to Albuquerque, Anthony.

09:41.048 --> 09:43.014
Or we do need
to discuss retirement.

09:43.016 --> 09:45.016
♪♪

09:45.018 --> 09:47.886
[<i> Camera shutter clicking</i> ]

09:47.888 --> 09:50.255
Mellie's camp wants to
know where we're at with
your convention speech.

09:50.257 --> 09:51.423
I'll have it
first thing in the morning.

09:51.425 --> 09:54.292
Mellie wants final approval
over content and length.

09:54.294 --> 09:55.894
It can be 20 minutes.
It can be 40 minutes.

09:55.896 --> 09:57.596
She'd like it
no more that 30.
Done.

09:57.598 --> 09:59.631
Mellie also wants you to speak
opening night of the convention.

09:59.633 --> 10:01.032
Not the final night?

10:01.034 --> 10:02.634
She wants that night
to herself.

10:02.636 --> 10:04.235
She thinks
it would better demarcate

10:04.237 --> 10:05.470
the past
and the future.

10:05.472 --> 10:07.539
I'm already the past?
In her mind.

10:07.541 --> 10:08.807
I get that.

10:08.809 --> 10:11.810
Thank you, sir,
for being so amenable.

10:11.812 --> 10:12.978
Figure what the hell?

10:12.980 --> 10:14.546
I'm out of here soon,
right?

10:14.548 --> 10:15.981
You make the White House
sound like prison.

10:15.983 --> 10:17.148
It is.

10:17.150 --> 10:19.050
But in five months...

10:19.052 --> 10:20.986
I'll be a free man.

10:20.988 --> 10:23.221
I'll be able
to go anywhere in the world.

10:23.223 --> 10:25.590
Maybe I'll write my memoirs
in Paris or London...

10:25.592 --> 10:27.225
or head back
to Santa Barbara.

10:27.227 --> 10:28.727
All nice options, sir.

10:28.729 --> 10:29.995
Who knows?

10:29.997 --> 10:31.496
Maybe I'll even end up
in Vermont.

10:31.498 --> 10:33.264
Vermont?

10:33.266 --> 10:35.233
It's a possibility.

10:35.235 --> 10:36.935
Yes, sir.

10:36.937 --> 10:39.604
Thank you, sir.

10:39.606 --> 10:42.841
♪♪

10:47.280 --> 10:50.081
So, what do you think about this
Admiral Jake Ballard?

10:50.083 --> 10:52.484
Eli Pope was pushing him
at that donor meeting,

10:52.486 --> 10:54.185
and the more I look,
the more I think

10:54.187 --> 10:56.921
he might actually be
a decent Vice President.

10:56.923 --> 10:59.290
Thought I'd run it by you,
get your take.

10:59.292 --> 11:01.993
My take?

11:01.995 --> 11:03.795
You've always got one.

11:03.797 --> 11:07.499
My take...my take...

11:07.501 --> 11:13.304
my take is that he's a soulless,
dead-eyed monster

11:13.306 --> 11:16.708
who murdered the love of my life
in cold blood.

11:16.710 --> 11:20.945
My take is that Jake Ballard
is a traitor

11:20.947 --> 11:24.282
to the nation I've spent my life
loving and serving.

11:24.284 --> 11:30.522
My take is that Jake Ballard
is Moloch, Abbedon, Leviathan,

11:30.524 --> 11:35.360
a serpent coiled at the feet
of his master Satan himself.

11:38.065 --> 11:41.199
Cyrus?

11:41.201 --> 11:43.635
What do you think about
Jake Ballard for VP?

11:45.238 --> 11:47.238
I think he'd be great.

11:47.240 --> 11:49.074
♪♪

11:49.076 --> 11:51.242
[<i> Camera shutter clicking</i> ]

11:51.244 --> 11:52.977
[ Elevator bell dings ]
David.

11:52.979 --> 11:54.379
I'm busy.
Doing what?

11:54.381 --> 11:55.814
I'm working.
On what?

11:55.816 --> 11:57.148
On a brief.
About what?

11:57.150 --> 11:58.316
How does this end?

11:58.318 --> 12:00.585
By you
telling me the truth.
About what?

12:00.587 --> 12:03.188
You met
with Cyrus Beene.

12:03.190 --> 12:05.156
How do you know
about that?

12:05.158 --> 12:07.826
What were you talking
to Cyrus about?

12:07.828 --> 12:09.427
[ Sighs ]
David?

12:09.429 --> 12:12.731
He wants me to be
Frankie Vargas' Vice President.

12:12.733 --> 12:14.165
I knew it!
This is great.

12:14.167 --> 12:15.200
Is it?

12:15.202 --> 12:17.001
Well, not for the country,
but for you!

12:17.003 --> 12:18.837
Well, when you put it
that way...

12:18.839 --> 12:19.838
I'm a Republican.

12:19.840 --> 12:21.372
I don't believe
in free college.

12:21.374 --> 12:23.408
I don't believe in free,
and I don't believe in college.

12:23.410 --> 12:24.909
Everything should have
a price,

12:24.911 --> 12:26.578
especially education,
which is worthless.

12:26.580 --> 12:28.079
I'm having trouble
following that.

12:28.081 --> 12:29.280
Hmm. Figures.

12:29.282 --> 12:30.949
Anyway,
what's yours?

12:30.951 --> 12:32.183
What's my what?

12:32.185 --> 12:33.418
Price.

12:33.420 --> 12:35.386
What's your price
to put me on the campaign?

12:35.388 --> 12:37.055
First of all,
there is no campaign.

12:37.057 --> 12:38.523
I haven't said
I was going to do it,

12:38.525 --> 12:40.725
and I'm probably<i> not</i>
going to do it. Second of all --

12:40.727 --> 12:42.927
You<i> are</i> going to do it
because if you do it,

12:42.929 --> 12:45.396
you<i> will</i> be Vice President
of the United States.

12:45.398 --> 12:47.732
You know Frankie Vargas
is gonna win this election.

12:47.734 --> 12:48.733
I<i> don't</i> know that.

12:48.735 --> 12:49.934
Oh,
you<i> do</i> know that

12:49.936 --> 12:51.569
because I'm going to vote
for Frankie Vargas,

12:51.571 --> 12:54.639
and I have a Golden Retriever
at home named Barry Goldwater.

12:54.641 --> 12:57.442
Second of all, I would never
bring you on to the campaign.

12:57.444 --> 12:58.443
Why not?

12:58.445 --> 13:00.078
Because you ruined
my life.

13:00.080 --> 13:03.114
Because you took away the one
person in my life I truly loved!

13:03.116 --> 13:06.284
You think you're the only one
who suffered in all that.

13:06.286 --> 13:08.620
I cried.
Multiple times.

13:08.622 --> 13:10.421
Tears.
In my eyes.

13:10.423 --> 13:12.724
You did that to me.

13:12.726 --> 13:14.826
Don't act like
you're the only victim here.

13:14.828 --> 13:16.294
You've made me
a terrible person --

13:16.296 --> 13:19.097
deceitful and power-hungry
and ambitious.

13:19.099 --> 13:21.666
I can't even believe
I'm considering this.

13:21.668 --> 13:24.002
You weren't working
out there.

13:24.004 --> 13:26.004
No.

13:26.006 --> 13:27.605
You were thinking
about becoming

13:27.607 --> 13:29.407
Vice President
of the United States.

13:29.409 --> 13:30.575
Yes.

13:30.577 --> 13:31.776
Do it.

13:31.778 --> 13:33.845
[ Inhales deeply ]

13:33.847 --> 13:38.283
If you're on the fence,
maybe this will help.

13:38.285 --> 13:39.918
No.
I don't want to.

13:39.920 --> 13:42.954
Well, I don't want to, either,
but this is where we are.

13:42.956 --> 13:44.189
We're debasing ourselves.

13:44.191 --> 13:45.456
Let's go
all the way.

13:45.458 --> 13:47.992
[ Scoffs ]

13:47.994 --> 13:49.027
Hey.
Olivia: Hey.

13:49.029 --> 13:50.662
So, I talked
to the President

13:50.664 --> 13:52.997
about everything Mellie wanted
at the convention.

13:52.999 --> 13:54.632
[ Sighs ]
I'm not sitting down yet.

13:54.634 --> 13:55.934
You don't have to.
He was fine with it.

13:55.936 --> 13:57.702
All of it?
All of it.

13:57.704 --> 13:59.137
He's even okay
speaking on opening night?

13:59.139 --> 14:00.171
I'm saying --
All of it.

14:00.173 --> 14:02.040
He surprised me, too.

14:03.643 --> 14:05.343
Got to go.

14:05.345 --> 14:07.679
[ Cellphone beeps ]

14:07.681 --> 14:08.847
Mr. President...

14:08.849 --> 14:10.782
Where did you
get this?

14:10.784 --> 14:12.150
Those are confidential.

14:12.152 --> 14:13.818
These are Liv's
medical records.

14:13.820 --> 14:15.787
Yes, sir!
Confidential medical --

14:15.789 --> 14:17.555
Where did you get
this file, Abby?

14:17.557 --> 14:19.157
Olivia's father
gave it to me.

14:19.159 --> 14:21.492
He was trying to lob a grenade
at Mellie's campaign, sir.

14:21.494 --> 14:23.695
No one knows,
and it needs to stay that way.

14:23.697 --> 14:26.364
Sir!
This is a lie.

14:28.235 --> 14:30.268
♪♪

14:36.543 --> 14:39.777
[ Knock on door ]

14:42.849 --> 14:44.315
May I?
No. Cyrus!

14:44.317 --> 14:47.151
Your father
just hijacked my campaign.

14:48.655 --> 14:50.255
Jake?

14:50.257 --> 14:54.525
He's forcing him onto the ticket
as Frankie's running mate.

14:54.527 --> 14:58.529
I was this close
to getting David Rosen the job,

14:58.531 --> 15:00.565
and now I'm giving it to the man
who killed my husband.

15:00.567 --> 15:01.900
You're a big boy,
Cyrus.

15:01.902 --> 15:03.501
Just say no.
I can't.

15:03.503 --> 15:05.737
What do you mean
you can't?
I mean I can't.

15:05.739 --> 15:08.573
What does he have
on you?
Doesn't matter.

15:08.575 --> 15:10.041
I can't help you
unless you tell me.

15:10.043 --> 15:12.076
Yes, you can.
What he has is irrelevant.

15:12.078 --> 15:13.578
Get out
of my apartment.
Liv!

15:13.580 --> 15:15.713
I have work to do,
and you're wasting my time.

15:15.715 --> 15:18.449
Liv,
don't do this.
Goodbye, Cy.

15:18.451 --> 15:19.951
Harrisburg!

15:19.953 --> 15:23.288
[ Sighs ]

15:23.290 --> 15:25.256
That shooting
in the Capitol.

15:25.258 --> 15:27.025
You know,
the hostage thing?

15:29.262 --> 15:31.696
That was...

15:31.698 --> 15:34.766
You set that up?

15:34.768 --> 15:35.967
Pretty good, right?

15:35.969 --> 15:37.235
[ Chuckles ]
[ Scoffs ]

15:37.237 --> 15:39.938
Well, "good's" not the word,
but it worked.

15:39.940 --> 15:43.041
Took Vargas from obscurity
to center stage overnight.

15:43.043 --> 15:44.442
You're talking
as if --

15:44.444 --> 15:45.977
People died.

15:45.979 --> 15:47.946
<i> Innocent</i> people!

15:47.948 --> 15:50.248
People were martyred.
For Jesus! For political Jesus!

15:50.250 --> 15:53.117
Don't joke about murder
and then ask for my help.

15:53.119 --> 15:54.986
Frankie Vargas
isn't just good

15:54.988 --> 15:56.888
and just
and smart and principled.

15:56.890 --> 15:59.390
He's<i> liked,</i>
Liv.

15:59.392 --> 16:03.127
That level of greatness
requires sacrifice.

16:03.129 --> 16:05.229
That's all I did --
Was help clear the path,

16:05.231 --> 16:06.731
lead him
on to the trek,

16:06.733 --> 16:10.802
and now, as I'm in the home
stretch in a two-horse race,

16:10.804 --> 16:13.137
your father
takes my horse,

16:13.139 --> 16:14.739
rides him
across the finish line.

16:14.741 --> 16:17.575
No. No.
That can't happen.

16:17.577 --> 16:19.844
This one is all on you.
<i> You</i> created this problem.

16:19.846 --> 16:21.412
You fix it.
On me?!

16:21.414 --> 16:25.016
Your father puts Jake
on the ticket and runs Vargas,

16:25.018 --> 16:27.285
you<i> know</i>
what happens.

16:27.287 --> 16:30.355
He finds a way to push me out,
then you lose the election.

16:30.357 --> 16:36.694
This election should be you
and me competing for the Oval --

16:36.696 --> 16:38.696
student versus master,
a fair fight.

16:38.698 --> 16:39.964
Don't you want that?

16:39.966 --> 16:41.699
You sure as hell should

16:41.701 --> 16:45.803
because the alternative is
you've already lost.

16:45.805 --> 16:48.773
♪♪

16:48.775 --> 16:50.508
[<i> Camera shutter clicking</i> ]

16:53.880 --> 16:57.815
[ Footsteps approach ]

16:57.817 --> 16:58.950
Have you seen this?

16:58.952 --> 17:00.885
Marcus: Mellie.
What?

17:00.887 --> 17:02.720
Fitz's convention speech.
It's an 8,000-word love
letter to himself.

17:02.722 --> 17:04.622
He never even mentions me,

17:04.624 --> 17:06.958
unless you count references
to the American people.

17:06.960 --> 17:09.160
We have to do something.
What are we gonna do?

17:09.162 --> 17:11.162
I don't know.
You don't know?

17:11.164 --> 17:13.131
[ Scoffs ]
That's it?

17:13.133 --> 17:15.199
You don't kn--
I know.

17:15.201 --> 17:17.201
I'm gonna talk
to Fitz.

17:19.406 --> 17:21.172
Marcus: He's angry.
Don't poke him.

17:21.174 --> 17:23.041
I was married to the man
for 25 years.

17:23.043 --> 17:24.709
Yeah, well,
that didn't work,

17:24.711 --> 17:26.310
so I'm just saying,
don't poke him.

17:26.312 --> 17:27.578
I'm not
gonna poke him.

17:27.580 --> 17:29.981
Your speech
is an abomination!

17:31.985 --> 17:34.052
You haven't heard it yet.

17:34.054 --> 17:36.054
[ Sighs ]
I've<i> read</i> it.

17:36.056 --> 17:38.556
You should give some weight
to the performance.

17:38.558 --> 17:40.992
Sure.
It'll be great.

17:40.994 --> 17:42.660
Hopefully,
nobody sees it.

17:42.662 --> 17:44.228
I am trying
to help you.

17:44.230 --> 17:46.097
By taking precious time
at my convention

17:46.099 --> 17:47.398
to talk about yourself?

17:47.400 --> 17:49.901
This is<i> you</i>
helping<i> me?</i>

17:49.903 --> 17:51.269
Yes.

17:51.271 --> 17:52.570
Yes?
Yes!

17:52.572 --> 17:55.673
The best thing
that I can do for you right now

17:55.675 --> 17:57.341
is to talk about me.

17:57.343 --> 17:58.776
I know
how that sounds,

17:58.778 --> 18:01.446
but if I talk about you,
that becomes the story.

18:01.448 --> 18:03.614
Am I being honest
about you, unfair?

18:03.616 --> 18:06.551
Did we strike a deal
for me to say the things I say?

18:06.553 --> 18:09.087
These are the questions
they are going to ask.

18:09.089 --> 18:10.922
We had a big,
messy,

18:10.924 --> 18:13.524
complicated,
very public relationship,

18:13.526 --> 18:15.259
and now we're divorced,
for God sake.

18:15.261 --> 18:17.428
I had an affair
with your campaign manager.

18:17.430 --> 18:19.564
I supported your opponent
in the primaries.

18:19.566 --> 18:22.266
What can I possibly say
about you on this stage

18:22.268 --> 18:24.235
that won't be
endlessly scrutinized

18:24.237 --> 18:26.204
and analyzed
and criticized

18:26.206 --> 18:28.639
and that won't leave you lost
in the process

18:28.641 --> 18:31.275
at the very moment
when you're supposed to shine?

18:31.277 --> 18:33.411
The best thing
that I can do for you

18:33.413 --> 18:35.313
is to simply remind
the American people

18:35.315 --> 18:37.248
how I've led this country,
how I've led the party,

18:37.250 --> 18:39.917
to burnish
the Grant name.

18:39.919 --> 18:42.253
That's what I can do for you,
so let me do that for you.

18:42.255 --> 18:44.555
You're treating me like
an unpopular

18:44.557 --> 18:47.291
first-term mayor
of Cincinnati, Mellie.

18:47.293 --> 18:49.827
I am the two-term
Republican President

18:49.829 --> 18:53.464
with massive political capital
and a 59% approval rating.

18:53.466 --> 18:55.299
I know
you don't get it,

18:55.301 --> 18:57.602
but they still love me
after everything.

18:57.604 --> 18:59.270
If it wasn't
for the Constitution,

18:59.272 --> 19:01.105
I'd be up here accepting
this nomination myself.

19:01.107 --> 19:03.975
So let me help you.

19:03.977 --> 19:05.510
You don't even see it,
do you?

19:05.512 --> 19:06.611
What?

19:06.613 --> 19:09.013
How arrogant you are,
how presumptuous.

19:09.015 --> 19:10.314
What?

19:10.316 --> 19:12.750
That you'd beat me.

19:12.752 --> 19:14.685
That wasn't the point.

19:14.687 --> 19:15.920
That<i> is</i> the point.

19:15.922 --> 19:17.355
Doesn't matter
how you dress it up,

19:17.357 --> 19:19.490
how cleverly you disguise it,
even from yourself.

19:19.492 --> 19:23.094
This is<i> all</i> about you.

19:23.096 --> 19:26.197
This is just
one more opportunity

19:26.199 --> 19:27.965
for you to talk about
how great you are.

19:27.967 --> 19:30.368
When you're running, you talk
about how great you are.

19:30.370 --> 19:32.870
When I'm running for office, you
talk about how great you are.

19:32.872 --> 19:34.372
Is there a scenario

19:34.374 --> 19:37.308
where you don't talk about
how great you are?

19:37.310 --> 19:39.844
You are standing up here
thumping your chest,

19:39.846 --> 19:41.179
reeling off your stats,

19:41.181 --> 19:43.381
chiseling yourself
onto Mount Rushmore.

19:43.383 --> 19:47.118
Like you didn't stand on my back
to get there --

19:47.120 --> 19:50.655
on Olivia's back, on Cyrus',
and your daddy's.

19:50.657 --> 19:53.958
I didn't have $100 million
trust fund, a political legacy.

19:53.960 --> 19:56.160
I didn't go to the best
boarding schools on the planet,

19:56.162 --> 19:58.829
and I am not
a white man.

19:58.831 --> 20:00.865
I am here on my own.

20:00.867 --> 20:03.734
I got here<i> on my own.</i>

20:03.736 --> 20:06.037
I got here...

20:06.039 --> 20:10.508
because I managed
to escape you.

20:10.510 --> 20:15.246
Like Liv
managed to escape you.

20:15.248 --> 20:16.514
[ Scoffs ]

20:16.516 --> 20:21.085
You talk about
what a great president you are,

20:21.087 --> 20:26.591
and yet you whined and cried
about how much you hate the job

20:26.593 --> 20:29.160
every chance
you got.

20:29.162 --> 20:31.162
Do those people out there
who<i> love</i> you

20:31.164 --> 20:33.931
know how many times
you tried to walk off the gig?

20:33.933 --> 20:37.768
How privileged
and entitled do you have to be

20:37.770 --> 20:42.873
to think of the most powerful
office in the world as a prison?

20:42.875 --> 20:47.078
Unlike you, Fitz,
I<i> want</i> this.

20:47.080 --> 20:51.749
Unlike you...
I earned it.

20:51.751 --> 20:54.418
And unlike you...

20:54.420 --> 20:58.422
I will not
squander it.

20:58.424 --> 21:01.359
This stage is<i> mine.</i>

21:02.795 --> 21:08.299
♪♪

21:18.645 --> 21:20.611
Liv.
Olivia: Sorry.

21:20.613 --> 21:22.713
This was the only way to meet
you without alerting my father.

21:23.950 --> 21:26.217
So Edison delivered
my message.

21:26.219 --> 21:27.285
You want out.

21:27.287 --> 21:28.919
I want
to help you.

21:28.921 --> 21:30.888
Good.
What's the plan?

21:30.890 --> 21:32.923
First,
I need you to know

21:32.925 --> 21:34.725
that what happened in the church
at your wedding --

21:34.727 --> 21:36.160
Please, no.

21:36.162 --> 21:38.095
Just the plan to escape.
What is it?

21:38.097 --> 21:39.897
I had to say
those things.

21:39.899 --> 21:41.299
It was the only way to --
Don't!

21:41.301 --> 21:42.667
I don't want anything
from you.

21:42.669 --> 21:43.968
Nothing.

21:43.970 --> 21:45.403
Except the plan.
A way out.

21:45.405 --> 21:46.904
You owe me that much
after --

21:46.906 --> 21:48.272
I'm trying to tell you
that it was the only way

21:48.274 --> 21:49.573
for me to keep my father
from killing you.

21:51.177 --> 21:53.477
Do you have a plan
or don't you?

21:55.481 --> 21:57.415
Not yet.
[ Scoffs ]

21:58.785 --> 22:01.185
I will save you.

22:01.187 --> 22:02.920
Somehow.

22:02.922 --> 22:04.455
But you're gonna have to
trust me

22:04.457 --> 22:08.292
because we cannot do this,
go against my father, divided.

22:08.294 --> 22:11.128
I have to know
that you trust me completely

22:11.130 --> 22:13.364
and believe me when I tell you
that everything I say

22:13.366 --> 22:15.633
and everything I do is in
your best interests to free you,

22:15.635 --> 22:18.369
to save you.

22:21.841 --> 22:24.108
Do you believe me?

22:24.110 --> 22:27.945
♪♪

22:27.947 --> 22:31.615
Tell me
you believe me.

22:31.617 --> 22:33.884
♪♪

22:33.886 --> 22:35.519
I cannot do this --

22:35.521 --> 22:38.189
Fine.
I believe you.

22:39.726 --> 22:41.792
Now do
whatever you have to do.

22:41.794 --> 22:43.961
Just get me out.

22:45.665 --> 22:47.298
[<i> Camera shutter clicking</i> ]

22:47.300 --> 22:48.632
Huck: You need to go
and take him, Liv.

22:48.634 --> 22:50.301
What?
If you want
to save Jake,

22:50.303 --> 22:52.336
you're gonna have to go
and take him.

22:52.338 --> 22:55.373
You can't sneak around back in
the dark and try and steal him.

22:55.375 --> 22:57.675
You have to go in through
the front door, lights on.

22:57.677 --> 22:59.143
That's insane.

22:59.145 --> 23:00.411
Like a gangster.

23:00.413 --> 23:02.480
Even if I could go through
the front door and take him,

23:02.482 --> 23:03.714
where would I put him,
Huck?

23:03.716 --> 23:05.216
Where does he go?!

23:05.218 --> 23:07.251
There's nowhere in the world
to hide from my father!

23:07.253 --> 23:08.419
You taught me that!

23:08.421 --> 23:10.421
Olivia: Jake is expecting me
to save him.

23:10.423 --> 23:12.490
He's waiting for me,
and we don't have a plan.

23:12.492 --> 23:13.591
[ Sighs ]

23:13.593 --> 23:16.093
♪♪

23:16.095 --> 23:18.129
[<i> Camera shutter clicking</i> ]

23:27.206 --> 23:29.173
[ Footsteps approach,
door opens ]

23:29.175 --> 23:30.708
Quinn:
We're all good.

23:30.710 --> 23:32.610
Doug Morton never existed.

23:32.612 --> 23:36.347
Anthony Musser, however,
is thriving in Albuquerque.

23:36.349 --> 23:38.382
New passport,
new driver's license --

23:38.384 --> 23:40.584
Great. We can announce Wagner
as VP now.

23:40.586 --> 23:43.287
Oh, for sure.
He's entirely 100% safe.

23:43.289 --> 23:44.522
[ Sighs ]

23:44.524 --> 23:46.357
♪♪

23:46.359 --> 23:48.092
What?

23:48.094 --> 23:49.226
Shh.

23:49.228 --> 23:51.595
Oh, boy.

23:51.597 --> 23:53.364
Explosive allegations concerning

23:53.366 --> 23:55.566
Governor Bill Wagner's past
emerged today.

23:55.568 --> 23:57.535
[ Indistinct shouting ]
Did you sell drugs
with Governor Wagner?

23:57.537 --> 23:58.903
Did Wagner
pay you to disappear?

23:58.905 --> 24:00.438
[ Camera shutters clicking ]

24:00.440 --> 24:02.606
<i> Information has surfaced</i>
<i> accusing him</i>

24:02.608 --> 24:05.109
<i> not only of dealing cocaine</i>
<i> as a college student,</i>

24:05.111 --> 24:06.877
<i> but of attempting</i>
<i> to cover up his actions</i>

24:06.879 --> 24:08.779
<i> by paying his former</i>
<i> drug associate to disappear.</i>

24:08.781 --> 24:10.648
Mellie:
Everything's going to hell.

24:10.650 --> 24:13.250
The convention's almost
here, and I don't even
have a running mate!

24:13.252 --> 24:15.152
What if I told you
I had the perfect person,

24:15.154 --> 24:16.287
somebody
who has everything

24:16.289 --> 24:17.721
we've been looking for
in a Vice President?

24:17.723 --> 24:20.257
I'd say,
"Great. Sign him up."

24:20.259 --> 24:22.660
You want to talk to him
about what?

24:22.662 --> 24:24.228
Mellie's VP pick.

24:24.230 --> 24:25.463
I need the President on board
before we announce.

24:25.465 --> 24:27.097
Right.

24:27.099 --> 24:28.432
Well, I'm not sure
that's the best idea right now.

24:28.434 --> 24:29.800
In fact, I don't even think
he's in his office.

24:29.802 --> 24:31.435
Charlotte!

24:31.437 --> 24:33.304
Uh, the meeting the President
had in the Roosevelt Room --

24:33.306 --> 24:34.472
he's still in there,
right?

24:34.474 --> 24:35.840
No, he's here.
Did you want to see him?

24:35.842 --> 24:37.274
Yes.
Sir?

24:37.276 --> 24:39.643
Olivia Pope's here
to see you.

24:39.645 --> 24:42.446
I was just telling Olivia
about your busy schedule

24:42.448 --> 24:45.015
and how this might not be
the best time to talk to her.

24:45.017 --> 24:49.186
It's fine.

24:50.790 --> 24:51.856
[ Door closes ]

24:51.858 --> 24:52.923
What can I do
for you?

24:52.925 --> 24:54.024
I wanted
to let you know

24:54.026 --> 24:55.292
that Mellie has chosen
a running mate.

24:55.294 --> 24:56.594
Fine.

24:56.596 --> 24:58.829
It's Jake.

24:59.465 --> 25:02.099
Jake Ballard?

25:02.101 --> 25:04.869
He's strong on national security
and foreign policy.

25:04.871 --> 25:06.804
He's good for her
geographically,

25:06.806 --> 25:09.440
and he polls extremely well
with both men and women.

25:11.043 --> 25:14.378
You want to sit?

25:14.380 --> 25:17.615
I really just came by
to tell you this.

25:17.617 --> 25:19.149
I figure
I owe you that much.

25:19.151 --> 25:20.484
You came by to tell me

25:20.486 --> 25:23.120
your ex-boyfriend's
gonna be on my ex-wife's ticket,

25:23.122 --> 25:25.956
and you won't sit
with me?

25:33.866 --> 25:37.868
[ Sighs ]

25:40.172 --> 25:42.072
I know
this is unexpected,

25:42.074 --> 25:44.241
but I also know
that you respect Jake.

25:44.243 --> 25:47.411
It's a good choice.
It is. I think.

25:47.413 --> 25:48.679
I mean...

25:48.681 --> 25:52.182
what do I know
about picking vice presidents?

25:52.184 --> 25:56.453
[ Chuckles ]

25:59.058 --> 26:00.691
[ Sighs ]

26:00.693 --> 26:02.526
I miss you.

26:02.528 --> 26:03.861
Fitz --

26:03.863 --> 26:05.829
Not like that.

26:05.831 --> 26:07.398
Like this --

26:07.400 --> 26:10.968
talking to you,
listening to you.

26:13.906 --> 26:15.940
Do you think
I listened to you enough?

26:17.543 --> 26:20.244
When? [ Chuckles ]

26:20.246 --> 26:21.745
When you were talking?

26:21.747 --> 26:23.047
[ Chuckles ]

26:23.049 --> 26:25.583
Fitz,
what's going on?

26:25.585 --> 26:28.719
Mellie says the entire way
I've handled this speech

26:28.721 --> 26:33.223
has been controlling,
manipulative, and narcissistic.

26:33.225 --> 26:36.226
I don't want to get in between
you and Mellie.

26:36.228 --> 26:37.227
♪♪

26:37.229 --> 26:38.929
[ Chuckles ]
You know what I mean.

26:38.931 --> 26:42.266
I'm sorry if I was that way
with you, too.

26:42.268 --> 26:44.802
I'm sorry
I didn't listen more.

26:47.707 --> 26:49.807
I am sorry.

26:49.809 --> 26:53.978
♪♪

27:01.988 --> 27:05.122
[ Inhales deeply ]

27:13.966 --> 27:15.499
I'm gonna change
the speech.

27:15.501 --> 27:16.500
Good.

27:16.502 --> 27:19.803
Why?

27:19.805 --> 27:23.207
Because she asked me to.

27:24.477 --> 27:30.381
[ Chuckles ]

27:33.486 --> 27:35.753
I support
your choice, Liv.

27:37.089 --> 27:40.624
[ Sighs ]

27:40.626 --> 27:42.126
Not that
you needed it.

27:42.128 --> 27:44.528
[ Chuckles ]

27:44.530 --> 27:46.997
Thank you.

27:48.668 --> 27:50.434
[ Door opens ]

27:50.436 --> 27:52.069
[ Door closes ]

27:56.776 --> 27:58.275
[<i> Camera shutter clicks</i> ]

27:58.277 --> 28:00.010
How did it go
with the President?

28:00.012 --> 28:01.779
Olivia: Good.

28:01.781 --> 28:04.515
Fine.
It was fine.

28:04.517 --> 28:06.550
So, it's still a go?

28:06.552 --> 28:07.785
Still a go.

28:08.788 --> 28:11.555
You don't sound convinced.

28:11.557 --> 28:12.990
What if Jake
doesn't come through?

28:12.992 --> 28:14.892
What if my father is two steps
ahead of me? What if --

28:14.894 --> 28:17.895
He has a saying, your father,
"You can't --

28:17.897 --> 28:20.664
"You can't take command."

28:20.666 --> 28:22.132
I know.

28:22.134 --> 28:23.734
And it's true.
You can't.

28:23.736 --> 28:27.071
You have to<i> become</i> command.

28:27.073 --> 28:31.642
♪♪

28:31.644 --> 28:33.310
[<i> Camera shutter clicking</i> ]

28:35.548 --> 28:36.914
He's an easy target,
Cy.

28:36.916 --> 28:39.483
I could leave right now and
be back with Ella in an hour.

28:39.485 --> 28:41.085
All you got to do
is say the word.

28:41.087 --> 28:44.154
Would he suffer?

28:44.156 --> 28:45.255
Depends.

28:45.257 --> 28:46.724
Is that
something you want?

28:46.726 --> 28:47.725
[ Sighs ]

28:47.727 --> 28:49.259
[ Water running ]

28:49.261 --> 28:50.728
What about Ella?

28:50.730 --> 28:53.330
Well, you'll...
hire a nanny.

28:53.332 --> 28:56.266
And then what?
Nannies need instructions.

28:58.504 --> 29:00.571
The last time
I put Ella to bed --

29:00.573 --> 29:02.840
I can't even tell you
when that was.

29:02.842 --> 29:04.675
What I need
is a new Michael,

29:04.677 --> 29:07.044
if I could replace Michael
with a new one.

29:07.046 --> 29:09.613
What about me?

29:09.615 --> 29:11.782
You?

29:13.385 --> 29:16.186
I found a baby once,
on a -- on a train.

29:16.188 --> 29:18.889
Cared for it
from Prague to Vienna.

29:18.891 --> 29:20.958
That's very sweet of you,
Tom,

29:20.960 --> 29:22.926
but I've read
"Of Mice and Men."

29:22.928 --> 29:24.795
I know
how that story ends.

29:24.797 --> 29:26.597
Hey, hey, hey, hey.

29:26.599 --> 29:31.802
[ Sighs ]

29:35.307 --> 29:39.476
The fact that we can sit here
and talk about murder

29:39.478 --> 29:42.880
and not
blink our eyes?

29:42.882 --> 29:45.382
I've never had that,
not with anyone.

29:45.384 --> 29:47.818
This the truest,
most honest relationship...

29:47.820 --> 29:48.819
I've ever had.

29:48.821 --> 29:51.255
♪♪

29:51.257 --> 29:53.924
And that's worth
far more to me

29:53.926 --> 29:56.493
than a man
who can pack a lunchbox.

29:58.097 --> 30:02.599
I can make it look like
an accident.

30:02.601 --> 30:04.067
No one
will be the wiser.

30:04.069 --> 30:05.736
Michael
will be punished,

30:05.738 --> 30:07.604
and you will have
your daughter back.

30:07.606 --> 30:10.707
♪♪

30:17.850 --> 30:19.416
[ Sniffles ]

30:19.418 --> 30:22.286
Sally:<i> Pressure --</i>
<i> some wilt, some rise.</i>

30:22.288 --> 30:24.788
<i> For others,</i>
<i> like myself, it's a drug.</i>

30:24.790 --> 30:27.191
<i> We enjoy it,</i>
<i> need it to perform.</i>

30:27.193 --> 30:30.627
<i> The magnitude of tonight's</i>
<i> event cannot be undersold.</i>

30:30.629 --> 30:32.696
<i> The pressure</i>
<i> on these candidates</i>

30:32.698 --> 30:35.165
<i> and who they choose to</i>
<i> stand beside them is crushing.</i>

30:35.167 --> 30:37.100
The coronation
is soon to come.

30:37.102 --> 30:40.838
I could not
be more proud of you.

30:40.840 --> 30:42.506
Frankie Vargas
and Jake Ballard --

30:42.508 --> 30:43.841
Now that's
a winning ticket.

30:43.843 --> 30:44.875
[ Door closes ]

30:44.877 --> 30:47.044
We should talk.

30:47.046 --> 30:49.379
Cyrus told you? [ Sighs ]
I knew he couldn't resist.

30:49.381 --> 30:50.681
What are you
talking about?

30:50.683 --> 30:51.982
Full of surprises.

30:51.984 --> 30:53.851
I'm here for Jake.

30:53.853 --> 30:55.052
Not sure
what that means.

30:55.054 --> 30:56.353
Those words
are innocuous enough,

30:56.355 --> 30:59.656
but the stance,
the tone I find alarming.

30:59.658 --> 31:01.225
Should I be alarmed?

31:01.227 --> 31:03.193
20 minutes from now,
ever wire service,

31:03.195 --> 31:04.862
every news outlet
in America

31:04.864 --> 31:07.698
will report that Jake Ballard
is gonna take the stage tonight

31:07.700 --> 31:09.399
as Mellie Grant's
Vice Presidential candidate...

31:09.401 --> 31:11.401
[ Laughs ]
...because that's
what I told them

31:11.403 --> 31:13.370
and because that is
what is going to happen.

31:13.372 --> 31:16.073
What?
Stand up, Jake.
Let's go.

31:16.075 --> 31:17.574
What is your angle?

31:17.576 --> 31:19.376
I mean,
this is stupid.

31:19.378 --> 31:21.979
Tell me,
what is your angle?

31:21.981 --> 31:24.681
No angle.
Jake is coming with me.

31:24.683 --> 31:26.350
Need I remind you of the words
that we exchanged

31:26.352 --> 31:28.719
on the day
of your brother's wedding?

31:28.721 --> 31:29.953
Jake, let's go.

31:31.924 --> 31:34.157
Jake,
this is simple.

31:34.159 --> 31:36.860
This is
what we talked about.

31:36.862 --> 31:39.363
♪♪

31:39.365 --> 31:41.198
All you have to do
is stand up,

31:41.200 --> 31:43.066
then you and I
walk out of here.

31:43.068 --> 31:47.337
♪♪

31:55.714 --> 31:57.948
[ Gun cocks ]

31:57.950 --> 32:01.551
Advise him,
Olivia.

32:01.553 --> 32:06.723
Advise him to plant
his narrow ass in that chair.

32:06.725 --> 32:08.659
♪♪

32:10.262 --> 32:11.561
I can't do that.

32:11.563 --> 32:13.297
It may look like
it's my finger on the trigger.

32:13.299 --> 32:14.765
It might look
I'm holding the gun.

32:14.767 --> 32:16.033
It's an illusion.

32:16.035 --> 32:18.402
You have your finger
on this trigger.

32:21.807 --> 32:23.807
You're in control.

32:23.809 --> 32:26.143
His life
is in your hands.

32:26.145 --> 32:29.846
♪♪

32:34.153 --> 32:36.153
Go ahead.

32:36.155 --> 32:37.254
Liv.
It's fine.

32:37.256 --> 32:38.622
Is it?
Go ahead.

32:38.624 --> 32:39.790
Kill your son.

32:39.792 --> 32:40.924
Shoot him.
Do it.

32:40.926 --> 32:42.459
Liv.
Do it!

32:42.461 --> 32:43.994
Is this how you pictured
your death, Jake?

32:43.996 --> 32:45.662
At the hands
of a woman

32:45.664 --> 32:47.664
you've done nothing
but love and protect?

32:47.666 --> 32:49.333
Come with me.

32:49.335 --> 32:54.071
♪♪

33:07.152 --> 33:09.186
He won't hurt you.
You're his son.

33:09.188 --> 33:12.022
♪♪

33:14.994 --> 33:18.695
Go!
Before I change my mind!

33:18.697 --> 33:21.832
[ Breathing heavily ]

33:24.870 --> 33:27.471
Damn.

33:27.473 --> 33:29.906
Damn.

33:35.547 --> 33:37.147
BNC now confirming reports
that Admiral Jake Ballard,

33:37.149 --> 33:39.182
<i> head of the NSA and close</i>
<i> friend of President Grant,</i>

33:39.184 --> 33:41.151
<i> is indeed</i>
<i> Senator Mellie Grant's pick</i>

33:41.153 --> 33:43.153
<i> to be her vice president.</i>

33:43.155 --> 33:45.655
Olivia, you clever, clever girl.

33:45.657 --> 33:48.725
Are you seeing this?

33:48.727 --> 33:49.960
I know.
We vetted him!

33:49.962 --> 33:51.495
I mean,
he was set.

33:51.497 --> 33:53.030
We're on the eve
of the announcement,

33:53.032 --> 33:54.398
and now we have
no VP.

33:54.400 --> 33:55.532
That's okay.

33:55.534 --> 33:57.501
<i> ...much-publicized</i>
<i> society wedding.</i>

33:57.503 --> 33:59.803
I know
the perfect guy.

33:59.805 --> 34:02.172
No, of course.

34:02.174 --> 34:04.508
Thank you.

34:04.510 --> 34:06.143
So?

34:06.145 --> 34:08.812
Is the call coming
from Frankie Vargas?

34:08.814 --> 34:10.414
Are you gonna be

34:10.416 --> 34:12.582
the next Vice President
of the United States or what?

34:12.584 --> 34:15.419
No.
It wasn't the call.
What?

34:15.421 --> 34:17.187
He decided
to go another way.

34:17.189 --> 34:18.588
Who calls saying
you're not getting the call?

34:18.590 --> 34:20.057
Who'd they
dump you for?

34:20.059 --> 34:21.658
No idea.

34:21.660 --> 34:23.427
All they said was that
it wasn't going to be me.

34:23.429 --> 34:25.796
[ Sighs ]

34:28.934 --> 34:31.701
How the hell
did you mess this up?

34:31.703 --> 34:33.503
[ Cheers and applause ]

34:33.505 --> 34:36.173
Fitz:
Thank you!

34:36.175 --> 34:38.175
We're here
to nominate a president...

34:38.177 --> 34:39.576
[ Cheers and applause ]

34:39.578 --> 34:41.845
...and I've got one in mind.

34:41.847 --> 34:44.448
[ Cheers and applause continue ]

34:44.450 --> 34:47.350
Sounds like you've got
someone in mind, too.

34:47.352 --> 34:50.353
You better be enjoying this,
Mellie Grant.

34:50.355 --> 34:52.456
[ Laughs ]
I am!

34:52.458 --> 34:55.992
...the next president
of the United States.

34:58.597 --> 35:02.199
Hey, hey, hey.

35:02.201 --> 35:03.400
I got your call.

35:03.402 --> 35:05.268
I mean, this isn't
the ideal place to kill him,

35:05.270 --> 35:06.470
but I think
I can make it work.

35:06.472 --> 35:08.472
And don't worry,
I won't do it in front of Ella.

35:08.474 --> 35:10.107
Michael and I
are getting back together,

35:10.109 --> 35:12.976
so that means
you and I are done.

35:12.978 --> 35:15.912
What is going on,
Cyrus?

35:15.914 --> 35:17.147
Between you and me,
nothing anymore.

35:17.149 --> 35:18.148
I'm sorry.

35:18.150 --> 35:19.282
Don't.

35:19.284 --> 35:20.951
Don't say that,
all right?

35:20.953 --> 35:22.619
Just tell me.

35:22.621 --> 35:24.821
Whatever I did, I can
make it up to you, I promise.

35:24.823 --> 35:26.990
It's not gonna work out,
Tom.

35:30.329 --> 35:33.663
Hey!

35:33.665 --> 35:34.731
You made it!

35:34.733 --> 35:36.166
We did.
[ Sighs ]

35:36.168 --> 35:37.634
Big night.
It is.

35:37.636 --> 35:39.402
I'm so happy
you're here.

35:39.404 --> 35:40.403
Hey, come on.

35:40.405 --> 35:41.838
Come on, come on!

35:41.840 --> 35:43.507
Let's go.
Let's go.

35:43.509 --> 35:46.610
Mellie Grant will be a leader.

35:46.612 --> 35:49.646
Mellie Grant will be a uniter.

35:49.648 --> 35:51.648
And Mellie Grant --

35:51.650 --> 35:56.086
well, trust me, everyone,
she was born to do this job.

35:56.088 --> 35:58.255
[ Cheers and applause ]

35:58.257 --> 36:00.724
[ Crowd chanting "Mellie" ]

36:04.696 --> 36:06.196
Jake.
Hey.

36:06.198 --> 36:08.165
What are you doing?

36:08.167 --> 36:10.433
What does it look
like I'm doing? I'm
getting ready for the game.

36:10.435 --> 36:12.035
[ Chuckles ]

36:12.037 --> 36:14.671
You realize you're meant to be
onstage in five minutes.

36:14.673 --> 36:16.206
I forgot to thank you.

36:16.208 --> 36:19.309
You stood up to Command,
stared him down.

36:19.311 --> 36:20.443
Far as I can tell,

36:20.445 --> 36:22.045
you're the first person
who's ever done that.

36:22.047 --> 36:24.181
Go big or go home,
right?

36:24.183 --> 36:26.316
Come on,
put your tie on.

36:26.318 --> 36:27.717
The President's
about to announce you.

36:27.719 --> 36:30.954
I don't want you
looking like a gigolo.

36:30.956 --> 36:32.189
[ Chuckles ]

36:32.191 --> 36:34.057
[ Sighs ]
Jake?

36:34.059 --> 36:35.825
I'm not coming.
What are you
talking about?

36:35.827 --> 36:37.327
[ Cheers and applause
in distance ]

36:37.329 --> 36:39.062
I'm taking myself
off the ticket.

36:39.064 --> 36:41.698
You're joking.

36:41.700 --> 36:43.200
There's no need
for it, Liv.

36:43.202 --> 36:44.968
I'm sitting here
practicing my speech,

36:44.970 --> 36:46.303
and all I can think
is "Why?"

36:46.305 --> 36:48.138
Why run for Vice President
when frankly,

36:48.140 --> 36:50.407
I'd rather flip patties
at Gettysburger.

36:50.409 --> 36:51.908
You'd be the second most
powerful person on the planet.

36:51.910 --> 36:53.743
And completely miserable.

36:53.745 --> 36:56.313
I-If I still feared your father,
yeah.

36:56.315 --> 36:57.747
Your name
is on the poster.

36:57.749 --> 36:58.748
We announced you.

36:58.750 --> 37:01.484
Check out this house
that's for sale.

37:01.486 --> 37:04.521
I drive by it every day
on my way to the office.

37:04.523 --> 37:06.156
It is the most normal,

37:06.158 --> 37:07.490
unremarkable house
I've ever seen in my life,

37:07.492 --> 37:09.859
and I desperately want
to live in it with you.

37:09.861 --> 37:11.228
Have you lost your mind?

37:11.230 --> 37:12.529
It's three blocks away

37:12.531 --> 37:14.264
from an equally unimpressive
high school.

37:14.266 --> 37:15.999
I can coach
their JV baseball team,

37:16.001 --> 37:17.500
help them reach
unimpressive heights

37:17.502 --> 37:20.170
while raising three
unimpressive kids with you.

37:20.172 --> 37:21.871
I'm running
a presidential race.

37:21.873 --> 37:23.340
Yeah,
and why is that?

37:23.342 --> 37:24.441
"Why is that?!"

37:24.443 --> 37:26.209
If it's to prove something
to your father,

37:26.211 --> 37:27.277
you've already done that.

37:27.279 --> 37:30.080
Come on, Liv!
Dare to be normal!

37:33.051 --> 37:34.584
Put the tie on.

37:34.586 --> 37:36.453
The world is our now.

37:36.455 --> 37:39.289
We can literally do
whatever the hell we want!

37:39.291 --> 37:40.857
Put the tie on!

37:40.859 --> 37:42.926
That's real power,
Liv.

37:42.928 --> 37:44.628
Not this other crap.

37:44.630 --> 37:45.962
[ Scoffs ]

37:45.964 --> 37:48.398
I have not gone through
what I've gone through,

37:48.400 --> 37:50.533
worked twice as hard
for half as much,

37:50.535 --> 37:54.204
only to end up living
an unimpressive life!

37:54.206 --> 37:56.906
Mediocrity is not an option
for me!

37:56.908 --> 37:59.776
I don't want that,
and neither should you!

38:02.080 --> 38:05.148
I see.
[ Cheering in distance ]

38:05.150 --> 38:09.085
So, it wasn't about
saving me at all, was it?

38:09.087 --> 38:13.056
It was about
saving your ticket.

38:13.058 --> 38:15.792
[ Cheers and applause
in distance ]

38:17.062 --> 38:19.596
I've gone
from being his bitch to yours.

38:19.598 --> 38:23.166
Put the tie on.

38:25.103 --> 38:28.171
[ Cheers and applause
in distance ]

38:28.173 --> 38:29.639
[ Olivia sighs ]

38:29.641 --> 38:33.176
♪♪

38:42.821 --> 38:45.922
Well, the time has come.

38:45.924 --> 38:48.158
It is my distinct honor
and privilege...

38:48.160 --> 38:49.659
[ Sighs ]
Thank God.

38:49.661 --> 38:51.127
All set?
...to introduce to you...

38:51.129 --> 38:52.762
You betcha.

38:52.764 --> 38:57.100
...your Republican presidential
nominee, Senator Mellie Grant!

38:57.102 --> 39:01.638
And the next Vice President of
the United States, Jake Ballard!

39:01.640 --> 39:05.308
[ Cheers and applause ]

39:05.310 --> 39:09.579
♪♪

39:11.183 --> 39:12.282
Have you heard?

39:12.284 --> 39:14.784
Vargas just announced
his running mate.

39:14.786 --> 39:15.785
Who is it?

39:15.787 --> 39:18.154
Abby,
who is it?

39:18.156 --> 39:19.856
[ Cellphone rings ]

39:19.858 --> 39:23.793
You were never gonna put
David Rosen on the ticket.

39:23.795 --> 39:26.196
David Rosen? God, no.
I'm trying to win, Liv.

39:26.198 --> 39:27.864
You used me.
Oh, please.

39:27.866 --> 39:30.400
This was a mutually beneficial
arrangement.

39:30.402 --> 39:32.635
We both got
the vice presidents we wanted.

39:32.637 --> 39:34.070
I can still
take you down.

39:34.072 --> 39:35.905
How would you
do that?

39:35.907 --> 39:37.374
One word -- Harrisburg.

39:37.376 --> 39:39.843
Two words --
Andrew Nichols.

39:39.845 --> 39:41.311
[ Cheers and applause
in distance ]

39:41.313 --> 39:42.746
Let's focus
on the positives here instead.

39:42.748 --> 39:45.582
One of us is getting back
to the White House.

39:45.584 --> 39:48.385
I got to run.

39:48.387 --> 39:51.554
Rauch: And Vice President
of the United States,

39:51.556 --> 39:55.558
Francisco Vargas
and Cyrus Beene!

39:55.560 --> 39:58.094
[ Cheers and applause ]

39:58.096 --> 40:03.099
♪♪

40:16.214 --> 40:19.082
[ Camera shutter clicks ]

40:24.923 --> 40:27.557
[ Cheers and applause ]

40:27.559 --> 40:30.927
♪♪

40:32.431 --> 40:37.233
I have spent a lifetime
keeping you safe from harm,

40:37.235 --> 40:39.035
a lifetime
worrying about your fate,

40:39.037 --> 40:40.370
a lifetime making sure

40:40.372 --> 40:43.239
that the path in front of you
was clear of debris.

40:43.241 --> 40:45.575
You are
Rowan's greatest achievement.

40:45.577 --> 40:48.945
You've become exactly the woman
he raised you to be.

40:48.947 --> 40:50.747
You have to be what?

40:50.749 --> 40:52.482
Twice as good.

40:52.484 --> 40:54.751
You held power
in your hands.

40:54.753 --> 40:56.319
You<i> were</i> power.

40:56.321 --> 40:58.087
You had the Oval.

40:58.089 --> 40:59.989
My baby
had the Oval.

40:59.991 --> 41:03.126
You will look
at all the possible outcomes.

41:03.128 --> 41:04.894
You'll understand
what needs to be done.

41:04.896 --> 41:06.162
You will pick a side,

41:06.164 --> 41:08.064
and then you will handle
this situation

41:08.066 --> 41:11.734
in the manner we both know
it needs to be handled.

41:11.736 --> 41:14.304
1600 Pennsylvania Avenue power.

41:14.306 --> 41:17.674
You will burn it down
and never look back.

41:17.676 --> 41:21.678
The apple does not fall
far from the tree, Olivia,

41:21.680 --> 41:23.680
poison though it may be.

41:23.682 --> 41:25.849
[ Cheers and applause ]

41:25.851 --> 41:29.752
♪♪

41:34.359 --> 41:35.325
Did you talk
to Cyrus?

41:35.327 --> 41:36.593
Yes.

41:36.595 --> 41:38.328
And?

41:38.330 --> 41:42.265
He said, "One of us is getting
back to the White House."

41:42.267 --> 41:43.800
He's right --
me.

41:43.802 --> 41:46.135
♪♪

41:46.137 --> 41:48.538
[<i> Cheers and applause</i> ]

41:48.540 --> 41:52.208
♪♪

41:55.113 --> 41:58.014
[ Crowd chanting "Mellie!" ]

41:58.016 --> 41:59.983
♪♪

41:59.985 --> 42:03.486
[ Cheers and applause ]

42:03.488 --> 42:05.722
♪♪

42:05.724 --> 42:08.725
And all it took was
a little nudge from your father.

42:08.727 --> 42:11.327
[ Chanting continues ]

42:11.329 --> 42:14.230
♪♪

42:20.639 --> 42:22.972
That's my girl.

